==== N E T W O R K I N G ====
http://wiki.libvirt.org/page/VirtualNetworking

Configuration to allow external machines to connect to guests.

1) Configure virtual switch to use Routed mode
2) Add routes in the physical network (this is required as no other hosts know about the subnet created by virtual switch)


1) Configure virtual switch to use Routed mode

 .) edit configuration
  # virsh net-edit default

   and change forward mode from nat to route
   <forward mode='nat'/>
   becomes
   <forward mode='route'/>

 .) stop network:
  # virsh net-destroy default

 .) start network:
  # virsh net-start default

2) Add route

http://www.thegeekstuff.com/2012/04/route-examples/

$ route add -net 192.168.3.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 gw 192.168.3.10
all the packets addressed to 192.168.3.* network will be forwarded via the 192.168.3.10 interface, which then delivers the packets to the addressed machine.





